                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-240" type="surname" value="KING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-240" type="given" value="HENRY JOSEPH"></interp>HENRY JOSEPH KING</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a Thames police-constable. On the 7th of Feb., about twelve o'clock in the day, I was with Shane at New Crane wharf, and saw the prisoner going along the shore, and climb up the gunwale of a barge, throw several lumps of coal down, then get down, put them into his basket, and take them to New Crane stairs, where I secured him—he said they did not belong to him but to another boy, who had run away.</p>
